ASABA – To boost economy and employment in the state, Delta State government has signed a shareholders’ agreement with Adventium Global Delta Consortium Limited for the transformation of the Songhai Delta Farm at Amukpe in Sapele Local Government Area into an Agro-Industrial Processing, Tourism and Training Park. The agreement is a Public Private Partnership (PPP) between Delta State government and Adventium Global Delta Consortium Limited, a subsidiary of Adventium Global Incorporation, USA. Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Patrick Ukah, who signed on behalf of the state government, stated that the signing of the agreement between the government and the consortium is line with the vision of Ifeanyi Okowa-led administration to create jobs for the teaming youths in the state while diversifying the state’s revenue base from over-reliance in crude oil revenue. He commended members of the committee set up to drive the process as they were able to deliver on the set goals within the stipulated time. He called on the management team of the consortium to ensure that they keep to the terms of the shareholders’ agreement to achieve the goals of the Public Private Partnership arrangement with the state government.